node.text:
#ad As you guys probably guessed I'm beyond excited that #WW84 is coming out this holiday season! It's a much-welcomed highlight as this year comes to an end. I can't wait to watch this movie (safely of course) with a small group of my family and friends in theaters! We’re counting down the days until we can reunite with our hero, Diana Prince. I'm already getting emotional just thinking about it! Mark your calendars for December 25 and don’t miss @WonderWomanFilm in theaters and streaming on @HBOMax!

I hope this video gave you a giggle! Are you as excited to see the movie as I am!?! @WBPictures

node.title: Wonder Woman 1984! SO EXCITED for the movie!

node.text: I quickly became such a fan of the show #Fleabag because of its witty nature, and awkward charm. I would be cracking up one minute then crying a few minutes later. Needless to say, I was really excited to partner with @AmazonPrimeVideo to recreate the main character! She is an amazing female character with so many dimensions – I loved bringing her to life in my own way! #sponsored

#WonderWoman1984 Cosplay ✨ before and after pic!

Would you guys be interested in a WW84 lookbook/guide video? Going through her different looks and breaking down the costumes? Lemme know! I love hearing your ideas! 🤗

node.text:
It's @johnnydepp 's & @natalieportman 's Birthday today! So I thought it would be a good excuse to share some cosplays of my fellow Geminis! ♊ (I threw in my Angelina Jolie cosplays too cause she's part of the Gemini club too 🤭)

Every costume/wig/makeup  in this post was all made, & worn by me!  I even have video tutorials showing how I made all of them! 

I already have 2 more Johnny Depp cosplays done that I havent really properly shared, & plans for more Natalie Portman and Angelina Jolie costumes as well! They all are such great actors and play so many awesome characters, it's really fun to keep finding new characters of theirs to dress as! Any suggestions??
